‘преступление’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Feist"/><biblScope>139 сл.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Pokorny"/><biblScope>818</biblScope></bibl>); %ill%i из %iry%i, как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_allon"/> ← *%iaryana%i-, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bællyn"/> ← *%ivarya-%i.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Maybe, it traces back to %ia-fery-on%i ← *%ia-parya-na%i- "unexperienced", "unprecedented"; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>πείρα</w> <gloss><q>trial</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w>πειράω</w> <gloss><q>I try</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w>έμπειρος</w> <gloss><q>tried</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/> <w>experior</w> <gloss><q>I try</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="gem"><lang/> <w>*firina</w> <gloss><q>something unusual</q></gloss></mentioned> → ‘crime’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Feist"/><biblScope>139 сл.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Pokorny"/><biblScope>818</biblScope></bibl>); %ill%i from %iry%i, like in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_allon"/> ← *%iaryana%i-, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bællyn"/> ← *%ivarya-%i.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>